/target
*.log
.env
.DS_Store

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

# RustRover
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBrains.gitignore that can
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this file.  For a more nuclear
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to ignore the entire idea folder.
#.idea/

# Raw SQLite stores are regenerated from their committed `.db.zst`
# siblings (see src/data/store.rs's resolve_store_path and
# src/bin/populate_embeddings.rs) — the uncompressed copies alone can
# exceed crates.io's 10MiB package limit, so only the compressed form is
# tracked.
mcp_store*.db
.fastembed_cache/
profile/
dhat-heap.json

# mcpify itself only ever writes .mcpify/settings.yaml and
# .mcpify/versions.json (see project_config::SETTINGS_RELATIVE_PATH and
# add_version::ledger::LEDGER_RELATIVE_PATH) — anything else that shows
# up there is scratch/backup debris from manual work, not reproducible
# project metadata, and shouldn't get swept into a commit by accident.
.mcpify/*
!.mcpify/versions.json
!.mcpify/settings.yaml
